cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

The paper deals with modeling surface properties and physical interactions in everyday scenes using sensor inputs and visual inference. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves learning end-to-end and inferring physical properties, which are common themes in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper introduces a new dataset and evaluates its model against baselines, which suggests that it may also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
